==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:11-->
The [[Image:FCGear_GearConnector.svg|24px]] '''FCGear GearConnector''' command combines two gear items …

==Usage== <!--T:4-->

<!--T:5-->
# Switch to the [[Image:Gear_workbench_icon.svg|16px]] [[Gear_Workbench|Gear Workbench]].
# Select two elements of matching teeth (See [[#Notes|Notes]]):
#* The first must be a spur gear or an internal gear.
#* The second can be a spur gear, or a rack
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[File:FCGear_GearConnector.svg|16px]] [[FCGear_GearConnector|Combine two gears]]}} button in the toolbar.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Gear → [[File:FCGear_GearConnector.svg|16px]] Combine two gears}} option from the menu.
# Change the gear parameter to the required conditions (see [[#Properties|Properties]]).

==Properties== <!--T:6-->

See also: [[Property_View|Property View]].

An FCGear GearConnector object is derived from a [[Part_Feature|Part Feature]] object and inherits all its properties. It also has the following additional properties:

=== Data ===

{{Properties_Title|gear}}

* {{PropertyData|angle1|Angle}}: Default is {{value|0°}}. Angle at which second gear is placed.
* {{PropertyData|angle2|Angle}}: Default is {{value|0°}}. Angle at which second gear is placed.
* {{PropertyData|master_gear|Link}}: Master gear.
* {{PropertyData|master_gear_stationary|Bool}}: Default is {{value|True}}. Master gear position is fixed (does not orbit).
* {{PropertyData|slave_gear|Link}}: Slave gear.
* {{PropertyData|slave_gear_stationary|Bool}}: Default is {{value|True}}. Slave gear position is fixed (does not orbit).

{{Properties_Title|version}}

* {{PropertyData|version|String}}: The freecad.gears-version.

==Notes== <!--T:7-->

<!--T:8-->
The selection order determines whether the second element can roll around the first element when the property {{PropertyData|angle1}} is changed.

